solution:
Chercher \( z \) tel que \( z^2 = i \). On pose \( z = a + ib \), puis on identifie :
\[
z^2 = a^2 - b^2 + 2abi = i \Rightarrow
\begin{cases}
a^2 - b^2 = 0 \\
2ab = 1
\end{cases}
\Rightarrow a = b, \quad 2a^2 = 1 \Rightarrow a = \pm \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}, \quad z = \pm \frac{1 + i}{\sqrt{2}}
\]
